body:
@jvivian pointed out there are s3 buckets left behind by some of the Toil tests. I'm pretty sure this issue has been addressed before so this is a regression. We should look at dealing with this in the Toil test base class.

┆Issue is synchronized with this [Jira Story](https://ucsc-cgl.atlassian.net/browse/TOIL-137)
┆Issue Number: TOIL-137

@cmarkello wanted to use the Azure job store, but the fact that to use it you need to put `azure:<account>:<container prefix>` doesn't seem to be in the documentation. I didn't find anything about the syntax for AWS either.

The syntax to invoke the different job stores, and the meaning of their configuration strings, should be prominently documented.

